<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="993" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d993">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Sultan of Turkey</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Yildiz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-01"><hi rend="italic">September 1,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have received with the keenest pleasure your excellency’s telegram
                            expressing your sincere felicitations on the occasion of the anniversary
                            of my accession to the throne. I beg you to accept my warmest
                            thanks.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Abdul Hamid.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>